Called Sam's Solution, found out they replaced the right front drive shaft due to a cv boot being torn, and replaced the left front axle due to internal fault. notes.note:
Good afternoon, thank you for your previous email with the estimate for the replacement of both front drive shafts on Tracey's 2019 Dodge Ram. Please be advised, the passenger side drive shaft is not covered as you mentioned that the reason it needed to be replaced was due to a torn cv boot. Tracey's contract stipulates that axle shafts are not covered in cases where the boot has torn. Fortunately she is covered for the left side axle shaft as it was an internal fault that occurred. The customer will be responsible for any diagnostics and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$315.00
Labour-$260.00 (2.0 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$28.75
Authorization-AJVW7SWY12

Total = $503.75

We already have the invoice for this repair, so I will send that down to our accounts payable team for payment.

Best regards,


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster

notes.note:
Good afternoon, thank you for your previous email with the estimate for the replacement of the transfer case input shaft seal. Fortunately this is a covered component under Claudette's contract. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, the contract allows for a maximum of $130/h for labour. If you choose to charge the customer $135/h, they will be responsible for the difference. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$26.13
Labour-$260.00 (2.0 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$24.20
Authorization-AHKL8HJWXY

Total = $210.33

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.


Best regards,


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
